<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.2.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" integrity="sha384-rbsA2VBKQhggwzxH7pPCaAqO46MgnOM80zW1RWuH61DGLwZJEdK2Kadq2F9CUG65" crossorigin="anonymous">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap-icons@1.10.3/font/bootstrap-icons.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/moreStyles.css">
    <title>info testing page</title>
</head>

<body id="info" class="d-flex h-100 text-center">
    <div class="cover-container d-flex w-100 h-100 p-3 mx-auto flex-column">
    <%- include("partials/header.ejs") %>
    

    <main class="lead py-xxl-5 mb-xl-4 text-center">
    <H1>Info Page</H1>
    <h2>Testing page to pull data from local JSON</h2>
    
    <div class="container-lg">
        <h5>The city that we travelled to: <%= places.city %> </h5>
        <p>We were travelling from <%=places.datetravelfrom %> to <%= places.datetravelto %> </p>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
        
    <p>The data come from a local JSON file and is being displayed onto this .ejs file. Although there aren't a lot here, I have also included a quick back button and a dark mode button here</p>
   
    <div class="d-grid gap-2 d-md-flex justify-content-md-start"><a class="btn btn-light text-decoration-none" role="button" href="/data">Back</a></button></div>
    <div class="d-grid gap-2 d-md-flex justify-content-md-end"> <button class="darkBtn" onclick="dark()"><i class="bi bi-moon" style="font-size: 1.5rem; color:black;"></i></button></div>
    </div> 
    
</main>

    <%- include("partials/footer.ejs") %>
</div>
<script>
 function dark() { 
       let element = document.body; 
         element.classList.toggle("dark");
         }
</script>
</body>
</html>
